I don't know the answer to your question.  I am inclined to believe that there was no direct CIA involvement in the overthrow.  I have just read a very interesting account of this period in Chester Cooper's book, &quot;The Lost Crusade, America in Vietnam,&quot; which goes through July 1970.  He states that the US had pulled a lot of funding and support from Diem, and made it known that we would be against a change.  &quot;The United States did not overtly encourage the generals, but it must have been very clear to them xf September that Washington was not opposed to a change.&quot;  He went on to say that &quot;The undisguised relief felt in Washington that at long last there would be a New Deal in Vietnam was tempered by disgust and horror at the final act of violence. (But not so in Saigon, where the deaths of the two leaders were either regarded with massive indifference or unrestrained glee.)<br><br>
